This paper is about a dataset for fine-grained sentiment analysis in Norwegian, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related areas. The paper also discusses experimental results, which suggests that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of annotation guidelines and inter-annotator agreement, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
